In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims January 16, 2016 as Religious Freedom Day in the United States. He highlights the importance of religious freedom as one of the country's cherished ideals and discusses the historical significance of religious freedom in America. The President emphasizes that the government does not endorse any particular religion and upholds the right for all individuals to practice their faith freely. He also mentions the government's efforts to protect religious freedom, enforce civil rights laws, and combat discrimination and hate crimes based on religion. Additionally, President Obama expresses the commitment to promote religious freedom globally and work with other countries to protect the rights of religious minorities. He calls on all Americans to commemorate Religious Freedom Day and safeguard this fundamental liberty for future generations.